  "soap_summary": "19-year-old female with ~<1 week history of dysuria, increased urinary frequency, lower abdominal achy pain, and pink-tinged urine. No fever reported. Exam/assessment: clinician suspects a simple urinary tract infection/cystitis (unconfirmed). Patient reports IBS (self-reported, unconfirmed) and an allergy to clindamycin. Current medications: combined oral contraceptive pill and mebeverine. Plan: arrange urine sample for testing, consider antibiotics if indicated (trimethoprim or nitrofurantoin discussed), advise hydration and paracetamol for pain, return if not improved or if fever/back pain/vomiting develop.",
